The paper focuses on enabling real-time robotic applications with energy efficiency on heterogeneous architectures, which falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of scene understanding and obstacle detection, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses managing multiple accelerators simultaneously, which is related to system architecture (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions energy savings, which is related to energy management (cs.EM).
